{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Keep the presumption of parental involvement & review fairness in family courts",
        "additional_details": "We are concerned that repealing the parental involvement presumption risks weakening children\u2019s right to relationships with both safe parents. We want processes to be reviewed to ensure fair evidence thresholds, accountability for proven false claims, and tougher sanctions for breaches. Family courts should not treat parents as suspects based solely on allegations. We believe unproven claims can trigger intrusive psychological and hair-strand tests, while contact orders may be breached without real sanctions.",
        "background": "We call on the Government to keep the presumption of parental involvement and review the fairness of family courts particularly when contact orders are breached or false accusations are made. Children need both safe parents.",
